headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic had 26 points, 19 rebounds and 11 assists for his 19th triple-double of the season, and the Denver Nuggets held on to beat the Charlotte Hornets 113-109 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic's triple-double lifts Nuggets past Hornets 113-109

headlines.description: — Darius Garland had 25 points and 12 assists, leading the Cleveland Cavaliers to a 107-101 win over the Orlando Magic on Monday night after losing big man Evan Mobley due to a sprained left ankle.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cavaliers beat Magic 107-101, lose Mobley to sprained ankle

headlines.description: — Bogdan Bogdanovic scored 29 points to lead the Atlanta Hawks past the Indiana Pacers 132-123 on Monday night.
— The worst losing streak of Miami's season is over. Not only that, but the Heat returned to the top of the Eastern Conference.
headlines.shortLinkText: Heat snap 4-game losing streak by topping Kings, 123-100

events.name: Chicago Bulls at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — The NBA's leading scorer in fourth quarters kept coming at them and the New York Knicks wouldn't buckle.
headlines.shortLinkText: Knicks hold off DeRozan, Bulls for 4th straight win

headlines.description: — Pascal Siakam had a season-high 40 points and 13 rebounds before fouling out, and the Toronto Raptors beat the short-handed Boston Celtics 115-112 in overtime on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Siakam scores 40 points, Raptors beat Celtics 115-112 in OT

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Houston Rockets

headlines.description: — Dejounte Murray scored a career-high 33 points and the San Antonio Spurs held on for a 123-120 win over the Houston Rockets Monday night to inch closer to the final play-in spot in the Western Conference.
headlines.shortLinkText: Murray scores career-high 33, Spurs outlast Rockets 123-120

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Memphis Grizzlies

headlines.description: — Desmond Bane scored 22 points, De’Anthony Melton and Dillon Brooks added 21 points each and the Memphis Grizzlies solidified their hold on second place in the Western Conference with a 123-95 victory over the short-handed Golden State Warriors on...
headlines.shortLinkText: Grizzlies beat Warriors 123-95, tighten hold on 2nd in West

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Isaiah Roby scored a career-high 30 points on 11-of-13 shooting and the Oklahoma City Thunder rallied in overtime to beat the Portland Trail Blazers 134-131 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Roby scores 30 as Thunder down Blazers 134-131 in OT
